cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SI, cs.LG. 

The paper presents a framework for video compressive sensing, which involves signal processing and image analysis. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves optimization techniques and information theory, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper applies the framework to dynamic MRI, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also involves sparsity and structured sparsity assumptions, which could place it under cs.SI (Signal Processing). Finally, the paper uses an optimization algorithm with theoretical guarantees, which suggests it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
